<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!-- App Sandbox disabled.
         Rationale: macMLX reads and writes `~/.mac-mlx/` (models,
         settings, logs, conversations, benchmarks, model-params) in a
         directory that must be shared with the unsandboxed CLI binary.
         Apple's "dotfile exemption" for `~/.<path>` is not reliable
         across macOS versions — sandboxed apps routinely hit
         "permission denied" when reading `~/.mac-mlx/models/` unless
         the user picks the path via NSOpenPanel first, which is a
         terrible UX for a tool that ships with a default model
         directory.

         LM Studio, Ollama, and oMLX all ship unsandboxed for the
         same reason. Gatekeeper + (future) notarisation remain the
         user-trust layer for a DMG-distributed app.

         ENABLE_APP_SANDBOX build-setting is also set to NO. -->
</dict>
</plist>
